WEBVTT

00:02.399 --> 00:04.267
CASSIE: This is me there.

00:04.301 --> 00:06.135
I did all the stunts.

00:06.168 --> 00:08.037
Some of the girls got picked
for their bodies,

00:08.070 --> 00:10.139
which you can see, I had one,

00:10.172 --> 00:12.008
and others for the gymnastics.

00:12.041 --> 00:13.710
But actually, I could do

00:13.743 --> 00:15.612
all the cheers.

00:15.645 --> 00:17.680
Cassie,

00:17.714 --> 00:18.981
these are wonderful photographs.

00:19.015 --> 00:20.016
Thank you.

00:20.049 --> 00:21.484
FRUTT: But you're going on trial

00:21.518 --> 00:22.719
for murder tomorrow,

00:22.752 --> 00:25.422
and I really think we need
to focus on the case.

00:26.723 --> 00:27.857
You said it was important

00:27.890 --> 00:29.492
that the jury feel
they know me a little.

00:29.792 --> 00:31.494
Yes, but whether you did

00:31.528 --> 00:32.795
your own backflips
in high school

00:32.829 --> 00:34.264
isn't relevant.

00:39.135 --> 00:40.169
We also need to meet

00:40.203 --> 00:42.305
with your housekeeper--
Nanny.

00:42.805 --> 00:44.641
Although she might as well be
a housekeeper

00:44.674 --> 00:47.544
since foster care
yanked away my son.

00:48.378 --> 00:50.280
This case could turn
on her testimony,

00:50.313 --> 00:52.482
so--
You think I did it, don't you?

00:52.515 --> 00:54.451
It's not our place
to pass judgment.

00:56.353 --> 00:58.221
What about the New Jersey
incident?

00:58.255 --> 00:59.489
As we explained,

00:59.522 --> 01:00.863
since you weren't
convicted there,

01:00.897 --> 01:02.299
the prosecution can't introduce

01:02.332 --> 01:02.999
it into--
CASSIE: I mean,

01:03.032 --> 01:04.766
do you think I did that one?

01:05.602 --> 01:06.703
I wouldn't know.

01:06.736 --> 01:09.171
I didn't!

01:09.205 --> 01:11.073
It was probably his wife.

01:11.107 --> 01:12.842
She did time in a rubber room,
you know?

01:12.875 --> 01:15.245
And for someone who supposedly
loved her husband,

01:15.278 --> 01:16.813
why wasn't she at the trial?

01:16.846 --> 01:19.015
Loved ones of the victims
always go to trial

01:19.048 --> 01:21.083
to see the murderer get theirs.

01:21.117 --> 01:23.520
Well, perhaps, as you say,

01:23.553 --> 01:25.488
she was the killer,
so she'd feel no need

01:25.522 --> 01:26.556
to see you get yours.

01:29.091 --> 01:31.961
YOUNG: We need to concentrate
on this trial.

01:31.994 --> 01:33.896
Who ran over who seven years ago

01:33.930 --> 01:36.733
in New Jersey isn't relevant.

01:36.766 --> 01:38.701
They're real.

01:38.735 --> 01:39.902
I'm sorry?

01:39.936 --> 01:40.970
My breasts.

01:41.003 --> 01:43.406
I can tell when women
are looking at them to see.

01:43.440 --> 01:44.707
They're real.

01:45.342 --> 01:46.543
So are mine.

01:46.576 --> 01:47.877
Is there a point?

01:48.945 --> 01:51.614
It's just that people think
I'm a fraud.

01:51.648 --> 01:53.283
The police obviously do,

01:53.316 --> 01:54.851
that's why I'm going on trial,
isn't it?

01:54.884 --> 01:56.386
And the jury's gonna think,

01:56.419 --> 01:57.654
"If she'd lie about her tits,

01:57.687 --> 01:59.522
then she'd lie about anything."

01:59.556 --> 02:01.898
Well, they're real.

02:01.931 --> 02:03.666
The jury needs to know it.

02:07.970 --> 02:09.972
(music playing)

02:58.321 --> 02:59.021
WOMAN: This way, please.

02:59.055 --> 03:01.998
(indistinct chatter)

03:03.333 --> 03:04.667
Here you go.
Thank you.

03:06.636 --> 03:07.570
Lindsay Dole.

03:09.005 --> 03:10.139
Ralph Alt. It's a pleasure.

03:10.172 --> 03:11.173
DOLE: Hi.

03:11.208 --> 03:12.775
RALPH: Ed Limato.
How do you do?

03:12.809 --> 03:14.043
DOLE: Nice to meet you.
RALPH: Brian Adams,

03:14.076 --> 03:15.512
Stanley Wells,

03:15.545 --> 03:16.779
and Roland Monroe,

03:16.813 --> 03:18.080
our client.
Pleasure to meet you, Lindsay.

03:18.114 --> 03:19.081
DOLE: Nice to meet you.

03:19.115 --> 03:21.284
Please have a seat.
DOLE: Thank you.

03:21.318 --> 03:23.152
RALPH: I know it was incredibly
short notice.

03:23.185 --> 03:24.721
I appreciate your agreeing
to meet with us.

03:24.754 --> 03:26.022
No problem.

03:28.225 --> 03:29.359
(sighs)

03:29.392 --> 03:32.061
Roland is CEO
of Seaboard Airlines,

03:32.094 --> 03:34.030
a fairly new East Coast
commuter service.

03:34.063 --> 03:35.265
I've heard of it.

03:35.298 --> 03:37.200
RALPH: They're being sued today
in federal court.

03:37.234 --> 03:39.101
The plaintiff,
a prospective passenger,

03:39.135 --> 03:40.203
is seeking a restraining order

03:40.237 --> 03:42.339
to enjoin one of Seaboard's
policies

03:43.473 --> 03:44.707
and we'd like you
to join with us

03:44.741 --> 03:46.609
and actually argue the motion.

03:46.643 --> 03:47.977
We can fully brief you
in all the issues,

03:48.010 --> 03:50.146
which are pretty
straightforward,

03:50.179 --> 03:51.348
assuming you're interested.

03:52.114 --> 03:53.182
Okay, what am I missing?

03:54.116 --> 03:54.951
Excuse me?

03:54.984 --> 03:56.919
This is a big law firm

03:56.953 --> 03:59.622
with plenty of high-powered
civil litigators.

03:59.656 --> 04:02.064
My practice has been almost
exclusively criminal.

04:03.366 --> 04:04.401
Why do you want me?

04:06.903 --> 04:08.438
We don't expect
to win the motion.

04:09.672 --> 04:12.309
Our goal is to attract
attention.

04:12.342 --> 04:14.611
Now, in addition to being a...

04:14.644 --> 04:16.144
pretty gifted attorney,

04:16.178 --> 04:17.279
you're attractive,

04:17.314 --> 04:19.216
and at the moment,
extremely hot copy,

04:19.249 --> 04:21.451
given your murder conviction
and recent release.

04:21.483 --> 04:22.252
Basically,

04:22.285 --> 04:25.322
we think you'll make the news.

04:25.355 --> 04:27.290
I want this particular policy

04:27.324 --> 04:28.124
to get some play.

04:28.157 --> 04:29.459
What's the policy?

04:30.059 --> 04:31.294
We don't fly Arabs.

04:33.095 --> 04:34.497
You're kidding, right?

04:34.530 --> 04:35.765
I'm not kidding.

04:35.798 --> 04:37.166
We wanna be known as the most

04:37.200 --> 04:39.502
security-conscious airline
in the new world.

04:40.670 --> 04:42.572
RALPH: Obviously, the longer
this thing stays in play,

04:42.605 --> 04:43.940
the more publicity it generates.

04:44.741 --> 04:46.676
Ideally, we'd like to get Roland
on the stand

04:46.709 --> 04:47.610
for an evidentiary hearing.

04:47.644 --> 04:49.145
If you can accomplish that,

04:49.178 --> 04:50.112
fantastic.

04:52.181 --> 04:53.783
You don't fly Arabs?

04:56.653 --> 04:59.055
She's a total loon, Eugene.

04:59.088 --> 05:00.297
Let's just do our job.

05:00.330 --> 05:01.331
What is our job?

05:01.364 --> 05:02.532
The directive from the client

05:02.565 --> 05:04.701
has been to authenticate
her breasts.

05:04.734 --> 05:05.835
Well, did they at least
take away

05:05.868 --> 05:06.936
her driver's license?

05:06.969 --> 05:08.004
Excuse me?

05:08.037 --> 05:09.672
When she ran over
her last lover?

05:09.706 --> 05:12.342
She wasn't convicted
of that, Lucy.

05:12.375 --> 05:13.610
(door opens)

05:14.577 --> 05:15.612
FRUTT: Sophie?

05:15.645 --> 05:16.746
I thought we were
gonna meet down

05:16.779 --> 05:17.547
at the courthouse?

05:17.580 --> 05:19.616
I know, but...

05:19.649 --> 05:21.651
can I talk to the two of you
for a second?

05:23.853 --> 05:25.688
I'm starting to panic a little.

05:25.722 --> 05:27.657
I don't think I should testify.

05:28.358 --> 05:29.959
Shouldn't testify?

05:29.992 --> 05:32.161
You're the alibi.
I know,

05:32.194 --> 05:34.030
but...

05:34.063 --> 05:37.200
I have a little skeleton
in my closet,

05:37.234 --> 05:39.035
and I am suddenly afraid

05:39.068 --> 05:40.570
that if the D. A. finds out--

05:40.603 --> 05:41.738
What skeleton?

05:41.771 --> 05:43.973
Four years ago, I...

05:44.006 --> 05:45.942
sort of changed my name,

05:45.975 --> 05:47.877
and not exactly legally.

05:47.910 --> 05:50.413
What do you mean you sort of
changed your name?

05:50.447 --> 05:52.582
I embezzled...

05:52.615 --> 05:53.383
a little

05:53.416 --> 05:55.117
from a former employer.

05:55.151 --> 05:56.986
It was nothing too serious.

05:57.019 --> 05:59.256
But my lawyer said
that there was a possibility

05:59.289 --> 06:00.330
that I could go to jail,

06:00.363 --> 06:02.499
so I fled the state

06:02.532 --> 06:03.733
and came to Massachusetts.

06:03.766 --> 06:06.503
And with the help of some
less reputable lawyers,

06:06.536 --> 06:09.239
I became Sophie Taylor.

06:11.308 --> 06:13.776
DONNELL: She tells you this
an hour before trial?

06:13.810 --> 06:15.512
BERLUTI: I'm not sure
you can call her.

06:15.545 --> 06:17.214
Why?
Because you can't knowingly

06:17.247 --> 06:18.915
put up a witness to lie.

06:18.948 --> 06:21.218
She so much as says
the name "Sophie Taylor,"

06:21.251 --> 06:23.052
it's a lie.
Look, the likelihood

06:23.085 --> 06:25.255
is the prosecution will have
no idea about this.

06:25.288 --> 06:27.724
She has no record
as Sophie Taylor.

06:27.757 --> 06:29.526
That isn't relevant
to the legal ethics.

06:29.559 --> 06:30.860
BERLUTI: What's her real name?

06:30.893 --> 06:32.128
She won't tell us.

06:32.161 --> 06:34.264
Jamie, maybe you and Lucy
could find that out.

06:34.297 --> 06:35.732
DONNELL: Why don't you just
plead this thing?

06:35.765 --> 06:37.334
We'd love to. Helen won't.

06:37.367 --> 06:38.968
The best they'll offer
is murder two.

06:39.001 --> 06:41.238
Then go with what you've got.

06:43.573 --> 06:45.808
This man is an American citizen.

06:45.842 --> 06:47.176
He's a college professor.

06:47.210 --> 06:48.678
The intent is safety here,

06:48.711 --> 06:51.814
not bias, and when--
KENDALL: Oh, come on, counsel.

06:51.848 --> 06:54.050
The assumption itself is a bias.

06:54.083 --> 06:55.518
To make an airline safe,

06:55.552 --> 06:57.487
you have to exclude Arabs?

06:57.520 --> 06:58.555
Your Honor, I will admit

06:58.588 --> 07:00.263
the outrageousness
of this policy.

07:00.297 --> 07:02.532
How generous of you.
Do you also acknowledge

07:02.565 --> 07:04.501
something called
equal protection?

07:04.534 --> 07:06.436
DOLE: The rich are already
doing this.

07:06.469 --> 07:08.137
They're chartering
private Gulf Streams

07:08.170 --> 07:09.606
to fly on Arab-free planes.

07:09.639 --> 07:11.774
One could argue my client
is serving equality

07:11.808 --> 07:13.175
by offering the same privilege

07:13.210 --> 07:14.010
to the middle class.

07:14.043 --> 07:16.145
One could argue it, I wouldn't.

07:16.178 --> 07:17.547
With the court's permission,

07:17.580 --> 07:19.582
I'd like to conduct
a short evidentiary hearing

07:19.616 --> 07:21.418
so you can hear directly
from my client.

07:21.451 --> 07:23.019
We don't need a hearing
to determine whether or not--

07:23.052 --> 07:24.454
DOLE: I will submit the laws

07:24.487 --> 07:27.424
in this area are complicated.

07:27.457 --> 07:28.758
If you're going to shut us down,

07:28.791 --> 07:30.627
I would at least request
the courtesy

07:30.660 --> 07:32.262
of hearing what my client
has to say.

07:37.300 --> 07:38.235
2:00.

07:40.570 --> 07:41.938
GAMBLE: Revenge is said to be

07:41.971 --> 07:43.973
the greatest of all motivators.

07:44.006 --> 07:47.677
There is no psychological
force greater,

07:47.710 --> 07:52.181
none than the will to get even.

07:52.215 --> 07:53.983
You will hear evidence

07:54.016 --> 07:55.151
how Cassie Ray

07:55.184 --> 07:57.287
and Jason Scott were lovers.

07:57.320 --> 07:59.322
They even had a child together.

07:59.356 --> 08:01.898
Then, early last May,

08:01.931 --> 08:03.766
Jason Scott broke it off

08:05.101 --> 08:08.305
and Cassie Ray became enraged.

08:08.338 --> 08:11.341
The evidence will reveal
the threats

08:11.374 --> 08:13.142
the defendant made
against the victim.

08:13.175 --> 08:16.446
The evidence will show
on May 23rd,

08:16.479 --> 08:19.081
in the middle of the night,

08:19.115 --> 08:20.650
Cassie Ray

08:20.683 --> 08:22.885
drove to the victim's house,

08:22.919 --> 08:25.855
picked up a baseball bat,

08:25.888 --> 08:27.089
and attacked the victim

08:27.123 --> 08:28.325
while he lay sleeping.

08:28.358 --> 08:30.627
The coroner will tell you

08:30.660 --> 08:33.062
Jason Scott was struck
on the head

08:33.095 --> 08:35.998
over 50 times.

08:36.032 --> 08:38.868
The expert psychiatrist

08:38.900 --> 08:40.203
will tell you

08:40.236 --> 08:42.438
that this inhuman brutality

08:42.472 --> 08:43.806
can only come

08:43.840 --> 08:46.409
from profound vengeance.

08:47.176 --> 08:48.311
Most of all,

08:48.345 --> 08:49.912
the evidence will reveal

08:49.946 --> 08:50.913
that this brutal murder

08:50.947 --> 08:53.049
was committed by Cassie Ray.

08:55.652 --> 08:57.554
The evidence will indeed reveal

08:57.587 --> 08:59.222
this was a brutal,
vicious murder,

08:59.256 --> 09:01.431
but that's all the evidence
will tell you.

09:01.464 --> 09:03.666
The evidence here is thin,

09:03.700 --> 09:05.067
circumstantial,

09:05.101 --> 09:07.304
no witnesses.

09:07.337 --> 09:09.406
Cassie Ray has an alibi.

09:09.439 --> 09:11.140
She was at home sleeping

09:11.173 --> 09:12.875
on the evening of May 23rd,

09:12.909 --> 09:14.777
and her nanny
will take the stand

09:14.811 --> 09:16.413
and tell you my client

09:16.446 --> 09:19.249
never left her house.

09:20.517 --> 09:22.352
Prosecution has a burden

09:22.385 --> 09:23.820
to prove guilt

09:23.853 --> 09:25.888
beyond all reasonable doubt.

09:25.922 --> 09:27.490
The evidence will reveal

09:27.524 --> 09:29.726
they can't even come close.

09:31.661 --> 09:33.796
What the jury
won't be allowed to hear

09:33.830 --> 09:35.131
is that Cassie Ray

09:35.164 --> 09:36.999
was arrested seven years ago

09:37.033 --> 09:38.735
for mowing down another lover

09:38.768 --> 09:40.437
with her SUV.

09:40.470 --> 09:41.971
Since Ms. Ray was acquitted

09:42.004 --> 09:43.172
of that murder,

09:43.206 --> 09:46.042
the information
is inadmissible.

09:46.075 --> 09:48.245
In other legal news,
Seaboard Airlines

09:48.278 --> 09:50.012
was sued today in federal court

09:50.046 --> 09:52.815
for its refusal
to allow passengers

09:52.849 --> 09:55.218
of Arab or Islamic descent

09:55.252 --> 09:56.753
on its aircraft.

09:58.788 --> 09:59.796
Well, they made the news.

09:59.829 --> 10:01.198
That's what they wanted, right?

10:01.231 --> 10:03.833
Lucy, is it okay
if I transfer my calls?

10:03.866 --> 10:05.502
I need to pick up
the little man at daycare.

10:05.535 --> 10:06.936
Sure.
WASHINGTON: Maybe you should get

10:06.969 --> 10:09.406
your own secretary.

10:09.439 --> 10:10.373
